-- China Owns 10% of Veolia Water UK After Sale, Sunday Times Says
-- B y   L i n d s a y   F o r t a d o
-- 2012-07-01T08:15:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-01/china-owns-10-of-veolia-water-uk-after-sale-sunday-times-says.html
China’s State Administration of
Foreign Exchange was among a group of investors that purchased
Veolia Water UK Plc in last week’s 1.24 billion-pound ($1.95
billion) sale, the Sunday Times reported, without saying where
it got the information.  The Chinese government now owns about 10 percent of the
British water company, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lindsay Fortado in London at 
 lfortado@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at   aaarons@bloomberg.net . 